Name: Name
Description: Simplified unique name of the player

Name: Current Cost
Description: Current cost of the player

Name: Current Cost x10
Description: Current cost of the player times 10

Name: Fixture Cost
Description: Cost of the player at the time of the fixture.

Name: Game Cost
Description: Cost of the player at the time of the fixture.

Name: Fixtures Ago
Description: How many fixtures ago from now a fixture was for each player. The last fixture is 1, the one before is 2, etc.

Name: Field Position
Description: Position of the player. Either GK, DEF, MID, FWD.

Name: Total Points
Description: Total number of points this season

Name: Selected?
Description: Is the player in the user's team?

Name: Captain?
Description: Is the player selected to be the captain?

Name: Vice Captain?
Description: Is the player selected to be the vice captain?

Name: Points Per Cost
Description: Total number of points divided by the player cost. This is can be an indicator for whether the player is undervalued or overpriced.

Name: Minutes Percent
Description: Percent of total number of minutes played this season compared to maximum played by any player

Name: Minutes Played
Description: Number of minutes the player has played this season

Name: Percent Selected
Description: Percentage of participants who currently have the player in their team

Name: Fixture Percent Selected
Description: Percentage of participants who select the player for this fixture

Name: News And Date
Description: News about the players and the date when it was added

Name: News
Description: News about the players

Name: News Date
Description: Date when news of the player was last updated

Name: Player Team ID
Description: ID of the team that the player is in that is unique across seasons

Name: Player Team Code
Description: ID of the team that the player is in

Name: First Name
Description: First name of the player

Name: Last Name
Description: Last name of the player

Name: Player Code
Description: ID of the player that is unique across seasons

Name: Long Name
Description: First and last name of the player

Name: Name and Short Team
Description: Name of the player and the short name of his team

Name: Chance Avail This GW
Description: Probability of the player will be available for playing the next game

Name: Chance Avail Next GW
Description: Probability of the player will be available for playing the game after next

Name: Team ID
Description: ID of the team for this season.

Name: Team Code
Description: ID of the team that is unique across seasons

Name: Team Short Name
Description: Short name of the team

Name: Team Name
Description: Name of the team

Name: Team Strength
Description: Rating of the team's strength on a scale from 2 to 5

Name: Team Short Name Home
Description: Team short name playing at home

Name: Team Name Home
Description: Team name playing at home

Name: Team Short Name Away
Description: Team short name playing at away

Name: Team Name Away
Description: Team name playing at away

Name: Team Last Updated
Description: The date/time when the data for this team was last loaded from the FPL API.

Name: Fixture Code
Description: ID of the fixture that is unique across seasons

Name: Fixture Strength Home
Description: Strength of the home team for a specific fixture

Name: Fixture Strength Away
Description: Strength of the away team for a specific fixture

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength
Description: Strength of this team relative to the opponent team for a specific fixture

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength Home
Description: Strength of the home team relative to the away team for a specific fixture

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength Away
Description: Strength of the away team relative to the home team for a specific fixture

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength Finished GWs
Description: Average relative strengths of all completed fixtures (higher values indicate lower difficulty)

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength Next GW
Description: Average relative strengths of the next fixture (higher values indicate lower difficulty)

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength Next 8 GWs
Description: Average relative strengths of the next five fixtures (higher values indicate lower difficulty)

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength GWs To Half
Description: Average relative strengths of all fixtures left up to half of the season or the end of the season if the second half has started (higher values indicate lower difficulty)

Name: Rel. Fixture Strength GWs To End
Description: Average relative strengths of all fixtures left for the season (higher values indicate lower difficulty)

Name: Is Home?
Description: Whether the team is playing at home or not

Name: Opp Team ID
Description: ID of the opposing team

Name: Fixture Short Name
Description: Short names of teams, e.g. ARS-BUR

Name: Fixture Short Name FDR
Description: Short names of teams with difficulty score, e.g. ARS-BUR (2)

Name: Rel Fixture Strength
Description: Relative strength of this fixture compared to previous ones. This generally a factor between 0.5 and 2. A factor below 1 indicates that this fixture is more difficult than the previous ones.

Name: Next GW
Description: Number of fixtures to the next game week for a specifc team. This is 1 except after the last game week. Note that there occasionally can be two fixtures in one game week.

Name: Next 8 GWs
Description: Number of fixtures to next five game weeks for a specific team. This is the minimum of 5 and the number of the game weeks left for the current season. Note that there occassionally can be two fixtures in one game week.

Name: GWs To Half
Description: Number of fixtures to the end of the current half of the season for a specific team. Note that there occasionally can be two fixtures in one game week.

Name: GWs To End
Description: Number of fixtures to the end of the season for a specific team. Note that there occasionally can be two fixtures in one game week.

Name: Total Points Consistency
Description: Consistency of the total point for the player up to the current GW. It is calculated as the average of the points relative to the maximum points and expressed as a percentage so that complete consistency results in 100%.

Name: Current Points Consistency
Description: Consistency of the total point for the player up to the current GW. It is calculated as the average of the points relative to the maximum points and expressed as a percentage so that complete consistency results in 100%.

Name: Total Points Recent Fixtures
Description: Total number of points that this player earned during the look back period.

Name: ICT Index Recent Fixtures
Description: Sum of all influence, creativity and thread index scores that this player earned during the look back period.

Name: Influence Recent Fixtures
Description: Sum of all influence points that this player earned during the look back period.

Name: Creativity Recent Fixtures
Description: Sum of all creativity points that this player earned during the look back period.

Name: Threat Recent Fixtures
Description: Sum of all thread points that this player earned during the look back period.

Name: Fixtures Played Recent Fixtures
Description: Number of fixtures that this player played during the look back period.. A fixture counts as played if the player played for at least one minute.

Name: Stats Completeness
Description: Fraction of available fixture information over the player fixture look back window.

Name: Stats Completeness Percent
Description: Percentage of available fixture information over the player fixture look back window.

Name: Selling Price
Description: Money received when selling player

Name: Purchase Price
Description: Money spent when buying player

Name: Transfers In This GW
Description: Total number of participants buying the player for the upcoming game week. This is the transfer number displayed on the home page in the transfers section.

Name: Total Transfers In
Description: Number of manager that transferred the player in since the beginning of the season.

Name: Transfers Out This GW
Description: Total number of participants selling the player for the upcoming game week. This is the transfer number displayed on the home page in the transfers section.

Name: Total Transfers Out
Description: Number of manager that transferred the player out since the beginning of the season.

Name: Corners & Ind. Free Kicks Order
Description: Rank of the player within his team for taking corner and indirect free kicks.

Name: Direct Free Kicks Order
Description: Rank of the player within his team for taking direct free kicks.

Name: Penalties Order
Description: Rank of the player within his team for taking penalties.

Name: Dream Team Count
Description: Number of time the player has been in the dream team this season.

Name: In Dream Team
Description: Is the player currently in the Dream Team?

Name: Form
Description: Average points the player received for each fixture played in the last 30 days.

Name: Profile Picture
Description: Name of the player profile picture.

Name: Goals Scored
Description: Number of goals scored by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Assists
Description: Number of assists to goals by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Clean Sheets
Description: Number of clean sheets that the player was awarded since the beginning of the season. Note that if a player does not play during a fixture with a clean sheet, the clean sheet count for this player will not increase.

Name: Goals Conceded
Description: Number of goals conceded while the player was playing since the beginning of the season.

Name: Own Goals
Description: Number of own goals scored by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Penalties Saved
Description: Number of penalties saved by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Penalties Missed
Description: Number of penalties missed by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Yellow Cards
Description: Number of yellow cards received by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Red Cards
Description: Number of red cards received by the player since the beginning of the season.

Name: Saves
Description: Number of saves the player has made since the beginning of the season.

Name: Bonus Points
Description: Number of bonus points the player has earned since the beginning of the season.

Name: BPS Score
Description: Score of the player since the beginning of the season according to the Bonus Point System (see https://www.premierleague.com/news/106533).

Name: ICT Index
Description: ICT Index as calculated by FPL based on the Influence, Creativity and Threat.

Name: ICT Index Rank
Description: ICT Index of the player compared to others as calculated by FPL. The lower the rank the better.

Name: Influence
Description: Degree to which the player has made an impact throughout the season as calculated by FPL. It takes into account events and actions that could directly or indirectly effect the outcome of the fixture. At the top level these are decisive actions like goals and assists. But the Influence score also processes significant defensive actions to analyse the effectiveness of defenders and goalkeepers.

Name: Influence Rank
Description: Influence of the player compared to others as calculated by FPL. The lower the rank the better.

Name: Creativity
Description: Performance of the player in terms of producing goalscoring opportunities for others as calculated by FPL. It can be used as a guide to identify the players most likely to supply assists. While this analyses frequency of passing and crossing, it also considers pitch location and quality of the final ball.

Name: Creativity Rank
Description: Creativity of the player compared to others as calculated by FPL. The lower the rank the better.

Name: Threat
Description: Threat of the player on goal as calculated by FPL. It gauges individuals most likely to score goals. While attempts are the key action, the Index looks at pitch location, giving greater weight to actions that are regarded as the best chances to score.

Name: Threat Rank
Description: Threat of the player compared to others as calculated by FPL. The lower the rank the better.

Name: Team FDR
Description: Difficulty score of the team (1: Easy to 5: Difficult)

Name: Started
Description: Whether the game has started

Name: Finished
Description: Whether the game has finished

Name: Field Position Code
Description: ID of the position that the player plays in

Name: Fixture ID
Description: ID of the fixture.

Name: Player ID
Description: ID of the player.

Name: Fixture Total Points
Description: Total points that the player was awarded for the fixture.

Name: Fixture Minutes Played
Description: Number of minutes the player played at the fixture.

Name: Fixture Cost x10
Description: The cost of the player at the end of the season in millions times 10.

Name: Fixture Goals Scored
Description: Number of goals scored by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Assists
Description: Number of assists to goals by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Clean Sheets
Description: Number of clean sheets that the player was awarded during the match. Note that if a player does not play during a fixture with a clean sheet, the clean sheet count for this player will not increase.

Name: Fixture Goals Conceded
Description: Number of goals conceded while the player was playing during the match.

Name: Fixture Own Goals
Description: Number of own goals scored by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Penalties Saved
Description: Number of penalties saved by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Penalties Missed
Description: Number of penalties missed by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Yellow Cards
Description: Number of yellow cards received by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Red Cards
Description: Number of red cards received by the player during the match.

Name: Fixture Saves
Description: Number of saves the player has made during the match.

Name: Fixture Bonus Points
Description: Number of bonus points the player has earned during the match.

Name: Fixture BPS Score
Description: Score of the player for the match according to the Bonus Point System (see https://www.premierleague.com/news/106533).

Name: Fixture ICT Index
Description: ICT Index for the match as calculated by FPL based on the Influence, Creativity and Threat.

Name: Fixture Influence
Description: Degree to which the player has made an impact during the match as calculated by FPL. It takes into account events and actions that could directly or indirectly effect the outcome of the fixture. At the top level these are decisive actions like goals and assists. But the Influence score also processes significant defensive actions to analyse the effectiveness of defenders and goalkeepers.

Name: Fixture Creativity
Description: Performance of the player in terms of producing goalscoring opportunities for others during the match as calculated by FPL. It can be used as a guide to identify the players most likely to supply assists. While this analyses frequency of passing and crossing, it also considers pitch location and quality of the final ball.

Name: Fixture Threat
Description: Threat of the player on goal during the match as calculated by FPL. It gauges individuals most likely to score goals. While attempts are the key action, the Index looks at pitch location, giving greater weight to actions that are regarded as the best chances to score.

Name: Fixture Transfers In
Description: Total number of participants who bought the player before the match.

Name: Fixture Transfers Out
Description: Total number of participants who sold the player before the match.

Name: Home Team FDR

Name: Kick Off Time

Name: Team Position

Name: Point Factor
Description: Multiplier for calculating the expected points at the team level. This value is 0 for players that are not selected, 2 for the captain and 1 for the rest.
